{
  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3ed8d0f3-7fff-f226-d12d-37406e64317b&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;The proposed roof extension, raised ridge and first-floor side extension, by reason of its unsympathetic scale, massing, location and detailed design, would comprise an incongruous, discordant and overly prominent form of development, to the detriment of the character and appearance of the site and adjoining terrace(s). It is considered that the proposal would be Contrary to Policies D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth) &amp;amp; D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) of The London Plan, as well as Policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 and the Council’s REA SPD (2009). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
